briefTitle: A Study of V503 Vaccine Given Concomitantly With REPEVAX™ in 11 to 15 Year Olds (V503-007)
officialTitle: A Phase III Open-Label Clinical Trial to Study the Immunogenicity and Tolerability of V503, a Multivalent Human Papillomavirus (HPV) L1 Virus-Like Particle (VLP) Vaccine, Given Concomitantly With REPEVAX™ in Preadolescents and Adolescents (11 to 15 Year Olds)
summary: This study will evaluate whether co-administration of the first dose of V503 and REPEVAX™ is well tolerated and causes a non-inferior immune response when compared to administration of REPEVAX™ one month following the first dose of V503.

primaryOutcome.measure: Geometric Mean Titers (GMTs) of the Antibody Response to Each of the Human Papillomavirus (HPV) Types Contained in V503
